.TH "e1000_read_flash_data_ich8lan" 9 "e1000_read_flash_data_ich8lan" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
e1000_read_flash_data_ich8lan \- Read byte or word from NVM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" e1000_read_flash_data_ich8lan
.BI "(struct e1000_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u32 offset "  ","
.BI "u8 size "  ","
.BI "u16 *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "offset" 12
The offset (in bytes) of the byte or word to read.
.IP "size" 12
Size of data to read, 1=byte 2=word
.IP "data" 12
Pointer to the word to store the value read.

Reads a byte or word from the NVM using the flash access registers.
